Diabetes UK conducts its business at all times with the highest standards of
integrity and honesty, and expects all its employees to maintain the same
Individuals working for Diabetes UK are therefore strongly encouraged to raise
any concerns that they may have about the conduct of others in the charity, or
the way in which the charity is run.
The Whistleblowing Policy (125 KB) provides further information on how staff
should report a concern, and sets out the ways in which Diabetes UK will
Please note: This policy provides specific information for Diabetes UK
employees only. Should you wish to raise a concern, or make a complaint, about
Diabetes UK as a member of the public, please contact us. For general
information on raising concerns about a charity, please visit the Charity
